casebody.data:
Elizabeth Scott, Respondent, v William H. Scott, Appellant. Submitted March 14, 1977; decided March 29, 1977

Reported below, 55 AD2d 674.

Appeal dismissed, without costs, by the Court of Appeals sua sponte, upon the ground that the appellant is not aggrieved by the modification at the Appellate Division (CPLR 5601, subd [a], par [iii]).
